%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%
\section{Prelim analysis}
%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%
\frame {                      % SLIDE

    \frametitle{Urgency ripples}

Reversion is indeterminate, so deadline may be pure suggestion \\
\textbf{Q:} Does action follow an urgency? \\
\textbf{Q:} Is it punctual?

\bigskip

Committee reporting may be good step to trace movement
\bi
\item Some urgencies may target bills in post-committee bottleneck---not all/most
\item Urgency compels a floor vote, so reporting committee(s) must consider and report
\item Bills with authorization must be referred to Hacienda committee, no exception
\ei

}
